WEBVTT


00:00:11.563 --> 00:00:13.105
Mr. Koyama,

00:00:13.188 --> 00:00:16.105
you are being charged with fraud.

00:00:16.605 --> 00:00:17.563
Detective,

00:00:17.646 --> 00:00:20.813
I swear I didn't deceive anyone.

00:00:20.896 --> 00:00:24.313
You know that yakuza
aren't allowed to stay at hotels, right?

00:00:24.396 --> 00:00:27.896
You booked a hotel room
under your name for Kiyoshi Kyogoku,

00:00:27.980 --> 00:00:30.313
the underboss of Fushimi-gumi.

00:00:31.271 --> 00:00:32.896
We even have evidence,

00:00:32.980 --> 00:00:35.855
thanks to the hotel security camera
catching it on tape.

00:00:36.605 --> 00:00:38.146
This is a clear case of fraud.

00:00:40.730 --> 00:00:43.730
Oh, you're remaining silent.

00:00:44.688 --> 00:00:47.396
I bet Attorney Kujo told you to do that.

00:00:48.271 --> 00:00:51.438
The police usually have all the evidence.

00:00:51.521 --> 00:00:53.230
But to prove that you intended

00:00:53.313 --> 00:00:55.021
to let Mr. Kyogoku stay there,

00:00:55.105 --> 00:00:57.480
they'll need you to confess.

00:00:57.563 --> 00:00:59.146
If you remain silent,

00:00:59.230 --> 00:01:01.688
the chances of prosecution are low.

00:01:04.855 --> 00:01:07.896
If you stay silent for 20 days,
you'll be cut loose.

00:01:12.146 --> 00:01:15.521
You know Tonohata, the driver working
for the escort service, right?

00:01:15.605 --> 00:01:17.271
He was kidnapped by someone

00:01:17.355 --> 00:01:20.480
and had his dick burned off
with a stun gun.

00:01:21.730 --> 00:01:24.355
He thinks that the business owner,
Kuga, punished him

00:01:24.438 --> 00:01:28.271
for laying hands on one of the escorts.

00:01:28.771 --> 00:01:31.938
And out of spite,
he set Kuga's car on fire.

00:01:32.980 --> 00:01:35.730
Detective, what are you talking about?

00:01:35.813 --> 00:01:39.271
But I'm thinking

00:01:39.355 --> 00:01:43.146
that you requested Kyogoku
to assault Tonohata.

00:01:43.230 --> 00:01:46.063
Huh? Why would I do that?

00:01:46.563 --> 00:01:49.146
Because you had a grudge towards Tonohata

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:52.396
for ruining your popular porn star
Shizuku Pien.

00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:55.813
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:02:00.355 --> 00:02:02.855
Then how about this?

00:02:06.771 --> 00:02:08.396
Manami Ogawa.

00:02:12.980 --> 00:02:14.480
Did you forget?

00:02:14.563 --> 00:02:19.938
She was the victim who was killed
by a minor ten years ago.

00:02:21.105 --> 00:02:25.063
She posted on social media
that she was dating you.

00:02:28.146 --> 00:02:32.188
I heard you were running something
similar to a pimp business back then.

00:02:32.688 --> 00:02:38.480
You were hooking up washed-up celebrities
with rich CEOs, right?

00:02:39.730 --> 00:02:43.146
Word is, some of the girls were minors.

00:02:44.813 --> 00:02:47.521
You were making elementary
and middle school girls work

00:02:47.605 --> 00:02:48.605
as prostitutes, huh?

00:02:50.646 --> 00:02:52.355
You scumbag.

00:02:53.646 --> 00:02:57.563
I heard there were politicians
and bureaucrats on your client list.

00:02:58.396 --> 00:03:02.063
You were afraid Manami Ogawa
was going to expose you,

00:03:02.146 --> 00:03:06.355
so you used Kyogoku to kill her
and shut her up, didn't you?

00:03:08.938 --> 00:03:10.813
The police are experts

00:03:10.896 --> 00:03:12.771
at making up stories.

00:03:12.855 --> 00:03:15.146
You could become a writer
after you retire.

00:03:17.355 --> 00:03:19.688
I feel bad for Manami Ogawa.

00:03:19.771 --> 00:03:21.396
But the culprit's been arrested,

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:22.688
and the case is solved.

00:03:22.771 --> 00:03:25.480
Why are you digging this up now?

00:03:31.521 --> 00:03:33.146
It's not over.

00:03:35.563 --> 00:03:38.521
Nothing about this case has been solved.

00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:52.813
Oh, I see.

00:03:54.021 --> 00:03:56.188
Now I get it. It makes sense.

00:03:57.980 --> 00:03:59.563
Come to think of it,

00:03:59.646 --> 00:04:03.188
Manami said she changed the bathwater
after her father used it

00:04:03.688 --> 00:04:06.355
because it grossed her out.

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:09.938
Fathers of women
who are grossed out by them

00:04:10.021 --> 00:04:13.480
are usually the type
who don't listen to their daughters.

00:04:13.563 --> 00:04:15.771
And they don't get along with their wives.

00:04:16.605 --> 00:04:20.230
Hearing their mothers badmouth
their fathers makes daughters hate them.

00:04:20.313 --> 00:04:23.063
Koyama, you have a daughter, right?

00:04:23.146 --> 00:04:25.313
Are you talking about your own family?

00:04:25.813 --> 00:04:28.438
If you make a living
exploiting women like that,

00:04:28.521 --> 00:04:29.980
your daughter will hate you.

00:04:30.063 --> 00:04:32.271
Are you discriminating
against my profession?

00:04:32.896 --> 00:04:36.980
There are a lot of women in my industry
who have problems.

00:04:37.063 --> 00:04:41.271
I listen to those who are sad,
grieving, suffering, and troubled.

00:04:41.771 --> 00:04:45.521
So I consider it my job
to listen to women.

00:04:45.605 --> 00:04:49.855
I have a very good relationship
with my daughter and wife.

00:04:49.938 --> 00:04:51.938
-Fukami, take him away.
-Yes.

00:04:58.938 --> 00:05:00.646
Mr. Arashiyama.

00:05:02.230 --> 00:05:06.105
You're obsessed with catching criminals,

00:05:06.188 --> 00:05:09.438
but I guess you were inattentive
to your daughter.

00:05:16.396 --> 00:05:21.146
Manami was one of those women
who you detectives usually deal with.

00:05:21.896 --> 00:05:25.980
She loved money and men
and made a living by selling her body.

00:05:27.271 --> 00:05:29.521
She was a dirty woman.

00:05:36.896 --> 00:05:42.938
Attorney Kujo, I'm totally shocked.
I'm super surprised.

00:05:43.438 --> 00:05:44.313
What?

00:05:44.813 --> 00:05:48.105
Detective Arashiyama turned out
to be my ex-girlfriend's father.

00:05:48.188 --> 00:05:50.480
They don't look alike at all.

00:05:51.855 --> 00:05:53.105
Is that so?

00:05:53.188 --> 00:05:56.355
The mystery of why
he's been so obsessed with arresting me,

00:05:56.438 --> 00:05:58.730
but not Mr. Kyogoku, is solved.

00:05:58.813 --> 00:06:02.230
His daughter was assaulted and killed,
and he resents me for that.

00:06:02.313 --> 00:06:04.355
I couldn't care less.

00:06:07.896 --> 00:06:09.813
I'm losing 20 precious days of my life

00:06:09.896 --> 00:06:12.271
because a police officer
is abusing his power.

00:06:12.771 --> 00:06:14.771
Her father's a pain in the ass,

00:06:14.855 --> 00:06:17.563
but honestly, his daughter
was also clingy and a pain.

00:06:18.146 --> 00:06:21.771
I got Manami pregnant.
I made her get an abortion immediately.

00:06:21.855 --> 00:06:24.063
After that,
she became over-the-top clingy.

00:06:24.146 --> 00:06:26.271
She's still a pain, even after she died.

00:06:26.771 --> 00:06:28.896
I don't like the way you talk.

00:06:30.438 --> 00:06:31.646
Regardless,

00:06:33.188 --> 00:06:35.188
I'll do my job properly.

00:07:21.146 --> 00:07:24.813
Thank you so much, Attorney Kujo.
You saved me.

00:07:33.771 --> 00:07:35.980
I'm back.

00:07:46.230 --> 00:07:48.438
I'm back.

00:07:49.438 --> 00:07:51.438
Welcome back, Attorney Karasuma.

00:07:51.521 --> 00:07:54.896
If you let out a big sigh like that,
happiness will run away.

00:07:56.021 --> 00:07:57.771
You're absolutely right.

00:07:59.063 --> 00:08:01.313
You seem tired.

00:08:02.855 --> 00:08:05.188
I look tired, don't I?

00:08:05.688 --> 00:08:09.938
Then, for a change,
I'll be the one to make you coffee.

00:08:13.355 --> 00:08:14.771
I'd appreciate that.

00:08:24.188 --> 00:08:26.688
I got these beans from my mom.

00:08:27.730 --> 00:08:29.980
Is this okay?
It's a gift from your mother.

00:08:30.063 --> 00:08:31.730
I don't have a grinder at home,

00:08:31.813 --> 00:08:33.980
so I thought I'd borrow yours.

00:08:34.938 --> 00:08:36.646
Then be my guest.

00:08:38.855 --> 00:08:40.980
Apparently, it's a blend my dad liked.

00:08:43.896 --> 00:08:46.605
I was a kid, so I never drank it.

00:08:46.688 --> 00:08:49.146
So I wanted to know what it tastes like.

00:08:50.896 --> 00:08:53.438
You always make me coffee,
so I just copied you.

00:08:54.021 --> 00:08:55.146
I hope it tastes good.

00:08:55.230 --> 00:08:56.771
Thank you very much.

00:09:02.063 --> 00:09:03.771
It has a gentle taste.

00:09:09.438 --> 00:09:12.230
The rooftop feels nice.

00:09:14.230 --> 00:09:16.355
It does.

00:09:21.646 --> 00:09:24.146
You've finally got
your usual look back again.

00:09:25.521 --> 00:09:26.355
What look?

00:09:27.355 --> 00:09:29.563
When you returned
from visiting Mr. Koyama,

00:09:29.646 --> 00:09:30.980
you looked terrifying.

00:09:33.355 --> 00:09:36.355
You should know better than anyone
what will happen

00:09:36.438 --> 00:09:38.271
if you continue to defend him.

00:09:52.938 --> 00:09:54.605
Yes, this is Kujo.

00:09:55.105 --> 00:09:56.813
Daddy, are you doing well?

00:09:57.688 --> 00:09:58.730
Rino?

00:09:59.521 --> 00:10:01.896
Mommy bought me a cell phone.

00:10:04.105 --> 00:10:05.521
That's great.

00:10:06.021 --> 00:10:07.480
Are you doing well, Rino?

00:10:07.980 --> 00:10:09.521
Yeah, I'm good.

00:10:09.605 --> 00:10:13.230
Good luck with work. See you.

00:10:20.355 --> 00:10:22.563
Your daughter is six, right?

00:10:22.646 --> 00:10:23.480
Yes.

00:10:23.563 --> 00:10:26.355
Then it must be a kid's cell phone
for security reasons.

00:10:27.105 --> 00:10:28.521
Yes, probably.

00:10:30.188 --> 00:10:31.396
What about it?

00:10:31.480 --> 00:10:35.980
With kid's cell phones, they can only call
numbers registered by their parents.

00:10:36.771 --> 00:10:41.480
So that means your ex-wife
registered your number.

00:10:45.646 --> 00:10:48.396
NEW CONTACT
RINO

00:10:48.480 --> 00:10:50.646
Maybe you'll get to see her one day.

00:11:08.813 --> 00:11:10.230
Koyama said

00:11:10.938 --> 00:11:14.688
Manami was a dirty woman.

00:11:15.188 --> 00:11:16.771
Koyashan said that?

00:11:17.271 --> 00:11:20.146
I couldn't say anything back to that scum.

00:11:20.855 --> 00:11:22.896
I'm pathetic.

00:11:23.646 --> 00:11:26.896
I can't believe my daughter
was being used by that scum.

00:11:28.480 --> 00:11:32.480
Young girls are easily swayed
by overly confident scum.

00:11:32.563 --> 00:11:36.813
They're easily fooled by people
who know how to present themselves.

00:11:36.896 --> 00:11:41.855
Even though it's an empty compliment
from scum, they still want it.

00:11:42.355 --> 00:11:44.355
Is that how it is?

00:11:45.021 --> 00:11:49.396
I realized that I really don't know
anything about Manami.

00:11:49.480 --> 00:11:51.771
You really don't know anything
about Manami?

00:11:51.855 --> 00:11:56.980
No. What her favorite food was,
what she enjoyed doing…

00:11:57.480 --> 00:11:58.605
I don't know anything.

00:11:59.188 --> 00:12:00.188
She liked KARA.

00:12:00.271 --> 00:12:02.480
Kara? Like an eggshell?

00:12:04.730 --> 00:12:08.438
No. The K-pop group
that was popular back then.

00:12:08.521 --> 00:12:10.438
I was a Girls' Generation fan.

00:12:10.521 --> 00:12:13.646
We used to sing karaoke all night long.

00:12:14.355 --> 00:12:16.188
She sings?

00:12:16.271 --> 00:12:17.105
Yeah.

00:12:18.396 --> 00:12:20.355
She sang really well,

00:12:21.521 --> 00:12:23.146
especially Hikaru Utada's songs.

00:12:25.355 --> 00:12:28.105
Manami would cry while singing.

00:12:30.605 --> 00:12:33.105
I can still picture it clearly.

00:12:35.313 --> 00:12:37.521
She was so thoughtful.

00:12:39.146 --> 00:12:40.146
And she was cute.

00:12:49.688 --> 00:12:51.938
You two really are father and daughter.

00:12:52.021 --> 00:12:53.271
What?

00:12:53.355 --> 00:12:58.396
Manami would put a lot
of seven-flavor chili powder on her udon,

00:12:58.480 --> 00:13:00.688
with a soft-boiled egg
and mixed tempura too.

00:13:09.480 --> 00:13:10.813
Miho.

00:13:13.063 --> 00:13:18.896
I appreciate that you remember Manami.

00:13:21.980 --> 00:13:23.230
Thank you.

00:13:28.521 --> 00:13:30.688
Daddy, I want this.

00:13:32.188 --> 00:13:33.021
Hmm?

00:13:33.896 --> 00:13:36.021
This? Where did you get this?

00:13:36.105 --> 00:13:36.980
Over there.

00:13:37.063 --> 00:13:40.146
Then let's ask Mommy if we can buy it.

00:13:44.355 --> 00:13:48.271
Daddy, I want this.

00:13:49.813 --> 00:13:51.063
No, Manami.

00:13:51.146 --> 00:13:53.396
No, I want it.

00:13:53.480 --> 00:13:55.521
Cut it out already.

00:14:04.980 --> 00:14:06.730
I'm sorry.

00:14:08.146 --> 00:14:09.355
Manami.

00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:17.063
I'm sorry.

00:14:19.230 --> 00:14:21.355
ORGANIZED CRIME DIVISION

00:14:23.355 --> 00:14:25.605
-Sir, do you have a moment?
-What is it?

00:14:26.188 --> 00:14:30.021
I asked Tonohata again if he recalled
anything about the day of the incident,

00:14:30.105 --> 00:14:32.230
and he said something interesting.

00:14:32.313 --> 00:14:33.146
What is it?

00:14:33.230 --> 00:14:36.896
He had a plastic bag over his head,
so he didn't know where he was,

00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:42.188
but he heard a rattling sound
like a compressor and smelled oil.

00:14:42.271 --> 00:14:45.313
Compressor and oil…

00:14:46.730 --> 00:14:50.146
That sounds like an auto repair shop.

00:14:50.646 --> 00:14:53.980
Detective Arashiyama,
you have a visitor again.

00:14:57.688 --> 00:14:59.021
THANKS FOR YOUR HARD WORK!

00:14:59.105 --> 00:15:00.855
Please have this for lunch.

00:15:03.230 --> 00:15:06.188
Thank you for going out of your way, Miho.

00:15:06.271 --> 00:15:10.730
I'm very grateful to you, Mr. Arashiyama.

00:15:11.230 --> 00:15:15.521
I've decided to move to a town
with better child-rearing support.

00:15:16.188 --> 00:15:17.063
Move?

00:15:17.646 --> 00:15:18.646
Yes.

00:15:19.480 --> 00:15:21.896
Meeting you, Mr. Arashiyama,

00:15:21.980 --> 00:15:25.355
has helped me to see life
in a more positive light.

00:15:27.813 --> 00:15:29.938
I see.

00:15:42.688 --> 00:15:45.896
DATING APP SCAM CASE
INVESTIGATION MATERIALS

00:16:25.646 --> 00:16:27.105
Mr. Arashiyama.

00:16:27.605 --> 00:16:30.021
What's the matter?
It's so early in the morning.

00:16:32.980 --> 00:16:35.063
I was getting ready to move

00:16:35.146 --> 00:16:37.355
and found some old pictures of Manami,

00:16:37.438 --> 00:16:38.730
so I was gonna send them.

00:16:38.813 --> 00:16:42.021
Oh, did something happen
with Manami's case again?

00:16:42.688 --> 00:16:44.980
Well, could you open the door?

00:16:51.563 --> 00:16:52.688
What happened--

00:16:52.771 --> 00:16:53.896
Miho,

00:16:55.271 --> 00:16:57.730
there's a warrant out
for your arrest for fraud.

00:16:57.813 --> 00:17:00.021
What? What are you…

00:17:00.730 --> 00:17:02.063
What? No, I… Ow!

00:17:02.146 --> 00:17:05.021
-7:20 a.m. Arrested.
-It hurts.

00:17:05.605 --> 00:17:08.980
-He actually arrested her himself.
-Detective Arashiyama is a demon.

00:17:09.063 --> 00:17:10.730
W-What's going on?

00:17:11.813 --> 00:17:14.771
I showed you the warrant
and explained the charges just now.

00:17:14.855 --> 00:17:17.563
I told you, I don't understand any of it!

00:17:17.646 --> 00:17:21.771
When we investigated you, we found
multiple reports of marriage fraud.

00:17:21.855 --> 00:17:23.813
It was your intention to deceive them,

00:17:23.896 --> 00:17:26.313
and you demanded money
after you misled them.

00:17:26.396 --> 00:17:28.480
-We have evidence.
-I don't know anything!

00:17:28.563 --> 00:17:30.730
We'll question you
at the station. Let's go.

00:17:30.813 --> 00:17:33.188
Wait, wait. What about my child?

00:17:33.271 --> 00:17:35.771
My baby will die without me.
You'll kill my child.

00:17:35.855 --> 00:17:38.063
We'll put the baby in a home,
so don't worry.

00:17:38.146 --> 00:17:40.146
I did a lot for Manami's case, didn't I?

00:17:40.230 --> 00:17:42.480
-Let me go.
-Okay, get in.

00:17:42.563 --> 00:17:44.063
That's a different matter.

00:17:45.938 --> 00:17:48.563
We catch criminals no matter what.

00:17:51.313 --> 00:17:53.438
No matter what.

00:17:55.605 --> 00:17:56.730
Attorney Kujo,

00:17:57.230 --> 00:18:00.313
Attorney Karasuma
came here alone the other day.

00:18:01.021 --> 00:18:02.521
Attorney Karasuma?

00:18:02.605 --> 00:18:07.063
Yes. He scolded me and told me
to stay away if I wanted to protect you.

00:18:10.980 --> 00:18:12.396
Is that so?

00:18:21.230 --> 00:18:22.396
What?

00:18:22.896 --> 00:18:26.313
Are you plotting something
with your lawyer?

00:18:27.271 --> 00:18:30.063
Detective Arashiyama, may I help you?

00:18:30.938 --> 00:18:32.563
I'm here as a customer.

00:18:32.646 --> 00:18:35.021
Fix the scratch on my car.

00:18:36.563 --> 00:18:37.605
Hey, Mibu.

00:18:38.605 --> 00:18:41.271
There have been a lot
of violent incidents around you.

00:18:41.355 --> 00:18:44.313
The assault on the driver
of the escort service, Tonohata.

00:18:44.896 --> 00:18:47.188
The assault with a blunt weapon
on the street.

00:18:47.271 --> 00:18:49.646
Kanemoto's drowning.

00:18:49.730 --> 00:18:54.105
And the murder committed ten years ago
by your younger associate, Inukai.

00:18:55.271 --> 00:18:58.021
You were involved
in some way, weren't you?

00:19:00.980 --> 00:19:04.855
This auto repair shop has a bad smell.

00:19:06.271 --> 00:19:09.563
The stench of death.
I smell the stench of death.

00:19:12.605 --> 00:19:13.688
Detective.

00:19:15.771 --> 00:19:17.105
If that's the case,

00:19:17.188 --> 00:19:18.771
why don't you go somewhere else

00:19:18.855 --> 00:19:20.188
to get your car fixed?

00:19:21.730 --> 00:19:23.938
We have the right to choose our customers.

00:19:24.438 --> 00:19:27.771
Criminals like you don't have any rights.

00:19:28.938 --> 00:19:29.771
Attorney Kujo,

00:19:30.730 --> 00:19:32.271
don't you hate yourself

00:19:32.355 --> 00:19:34.688
for helping such heartless people?

00:19:35.646 --> 00:19:38.146
Attorneys don't protect bad people.

00:19:38.646 --> 00:19:40.480
We protect the procedure.

00:19:41.563 --> 00:19:44.271
The procedure? What do you mean?

00:19:44.938 --> 00:19:47.313
I doubt you police officers
would understand,

00:19:47.396 --> 00:19:49.563
but we carry out
proper criminal procedures.

00:19:49.646 --> 00:19:52.813
Do you consider being
the criminals' lapdog "proper procedure"?

00:19:52.896 --> 00:19:56.771
All I'm saying is another attorney
would have to take this case if I didn't.

00:19:56.855 --> 00:19:59.605
That doesn't mean
telling criminals to remain silent.

00:19:59.688 --> 00:20:01.021
You're supporting crimes.

00:20:01.105 --> 00:20:05.230
The Constitution and the Code of Criminal
Procedure guarantee the right to silence.

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:08.605
Study the Constitution
and the Code of Criminal Procedure.

00:20:13.563 --> 00:20:15.896
Well, then, Attorney Kujo…

00:20:17.688 --> 00:20:20.813
if your daughter
was assaulted and murdered,

00:20:20.896 --> 00:20:23.021
could you defend the criminal
the same way?

00:20:28.146 --> 00:20:32.480
An attorney's mission is to achieve
social justice and protect human rights.

00:20:32.563 --> 00:20:35.021
As a pro, I believe
I should step aside from cases

00:20:35.105 --> 00:20:37.230
where my emotions could cloud my judgment.

00:20:38.563 --> 00:20:41.855
The police and attorneys
have different roles as professionals,

00:20:41.938 --> 00:20:44.105
but we share the same goal.

00:20:44.188 --> 00:20:46.355
A peaceful society, right?

00:20:48.730 --> 00:20:52.063
The lapdog of anti-social forces
is spouting sophistry.

00:20:53.396 --> 00:20:56.813
I'll get you busted along with Mibu,
so you'd better be prepared.

00:21:02.855 --> 00:21:08.230
If my daughter was murdered,
I wouldn't want to leave it to the courts.

00:21:10.605 --> 00:21:11.855
Aren't they beautiful?

00:21:12.730 --> 00:21:13.563
Huh?

00:21:14.271 --> 00:21:15.396
The flowers.

00:21:17.063 --> 00:21:18.521
Oh, did you buy these, Mom?

00:21:18.605 --> 00:21:22.688
Yes. I took a little walk
to the front of the station.

00:21:24.021 --> 00:21:27.355
I passed by a flower shop,
and I liked them.

00:21:27.438 --> 00:21:28.438
I see.

00:21:28.521 --> 00:21:29.521
Here you go.

00:21:29.605 --> 00:21:30.521
Thank you.

00:21:34.813 --> 00:21:36.271
Omurice?

00:21:36.938 --> 00:21:39.688
This is what we always ate
when you needed cheering up.

00:21:40.188 --> 00:21:42.146
Do I look like I'm down?

00:21:42.813 --> 00:21:45.105
Here, eat up.

00:21:46.688 --> 00:21:48.313
Thank you for the food.

00:21:53.396 --> 00:21:56.063
It's been a long time
since I've made it. How is it?

00:21:57.105 --> 00:21:57.938
It's delicious.

00:21:59.396 --> 00:22:00.938
And nostalgic.

00:22:01.438 --> 00:22:03.355
Before exams and competitions,

00:22:03.438 --> 00:22:05.646
I ate this a lot when I needed a boost.

00:22:09.563 --> 00:22:10.521
What happened?

00:22:13.938 --> 00:22:15.521
Well, a lot of things.

00:22:15.605 --> 00:22:16.605
What kind of things?

00:22:16.688 --> 00:22:20.688
By the way, I had the coffee you gave me
with Attorney Kujo the other day.

00:22:20.771 --> 00:22:22.313
He said it was delicious.

00:22:22.938 --> 00:22:24.021
Really?

00:22:24.605 --> 00:22:28.480
I have to go say hi to Attorney Kujo.

00:22:29.771 --> 00:22:32.480
It's okay. I'm not a child.

00:22:33.021 --> 00:22:34.063
You should eat too.

00:22:34.146 --> 00:22:37.438
Okay. But before that…

00:22:44.188 --> 00:22:47.938
We had omurice with Dad
before field day, remember?

00:22:48.938 --> 00:22:51.396
He was ecstatic
about the parent-child relay race.

00:22:51.896 --> 00:22:54.646
Thanks to the omurice,
we came in first place.

00:22:55.605 --> 00:22:57.313
Your dad used to say

00:22:58.355 --> 00:23:01.563
that omurice is our family's lucky meal.

00:23:03.646 --> 00:23:06.563
He said, "I have an important
business trip today."

00:23:07.813 --> 00:23:09.188
"So this morning…

00:23:11.230 --> 00:23:13.271
I want omurice," he said.

00:23:15.896 --> 00:23:16.730
That day…

00:23:19.438 --> 00:23:21.188
That was the last time.

00:23:25.605 --> 00:23:26.688
Mom?

00:23:34.646 --> 00:23:35.730
Mom.

00:23:38.105 --> 00:23:40.105
He said he'd be back late.

00:23:41.646 --> 00:23:43.771
But I never thought he wouldn't come back.

00:23:46.396 --> 00:23:48.105
He's never coming back.

00:23:48.771 --> 00:23:50.105
He's gone.

00:23:51.521 --> 00:23:52.730
But why?

00:23:54.855 --> 00:23:57.438
Why did they write
such an article about your dad?

00:24:01.521 --> 00:24:03.230
I was so scared.

00:24:04.271 --> 00:24:06.771
But no one helped us.

00:24:07.355 --> 00:24:09.730
I didn't want to know anything.

00:24:10.938 --> 00:24:13.438
I only wanted your dad that we knew.

00:24:13.521 --> 00:24:15.146
You shouldn't remember.

00:24:15.230 --> 00:24:17.188
After your dad was gone,

00:24:18.730 --> 00:24:19.980
you were the only…

00:24:20.063 --> 00:24:20.938
It's okay, Mom.

00:24:21.021 --> 00:24:22.438
I made a promise to him!

00:24:22.521 --> 00:24:26.396
I'll never do anything
that will make you sad, Mom.

00:24:35.480 --> 00:24:37.563
Mom, you said before

00:24:39.105 --> 00:24:43.438
that Dad wanted me
to be someone who helps others.

00:24:47.188 --> 00:24:48.563
I promise.

00:24:50.188 --> 00:24:51.480
So don't worry.

00:24:56.146 --> 00:24:57.563
I'll come again.

00:24:58.646 --> 00:25:00.021
Shinji,

00:25:00.563 --> 00:25:03.146
I want to see Attorney Kujo.

00:25:03.813 --> 00:25:04.730
Attorney Kujo?

00:25:07.063 --> 00:25:09.105
He's the one making you suffer, right?

00:25:12.355 --> 00:25:13.813
It's a promise.

00:25:35.396 --> 00:25:37.521
I'm back.

00:25:37.605 --> 00:25:39.105
Welcome back.

00:25:40.813 --> 00:25:41.938
Attorney Karasuma.

00:25:42.021 --> 00:25:42.938
Yes?

00:25:44.021 --> 00:25:45.271
This was on the floor.

00:25:48.896 --> 00:25:50.480
O-Oh, thank you.

00:25:50.563 --> 00:25:51.771
What is that pen?

00:25:51.855 --> 00:25:53.063
You don't need to know.

00:25:53.646 --> 00:25:56.480
-Is there something special about it?
-There's nothing!

00:25:58.355 --> 00:26:00.855
Ms. Yakushimae,
are you slacking off here again?

00:26:01.605 --> 00:26:05.563
Speak for yourself, Attorney Karasuma.
Where have you been wandering around?

00:26:05.646 --> 00:26:07.146
I stopped by my parents' home.

00:26:08.021 --> 00:26:09.938
If it was for your parents, it's okay.

00:26:10.021 --> 00:26:12.855
Would you like to take a break
after a bit of work?

00:26:12.938 --> 00:26:17.605
Shall I make the coffee
that your mother gave us the other day?

00:26:17.688 --> 00:26:22.063
When I told my mother that you said
it was delicious, she was happy.

00:26:22.146 --> 00:26:23.146
It was exquisite.

00:26:25.146 --> 00:26:26.230
Attorney Kujo,

00:26:26.730 --> 00:26:32.063
my mother said she would like to meet you.

00:26:32.605 --> 00:26:33.646
Is that so?

00:26:33.730 --> 00:26:35.521
She made me promise.

00:26:40.105 --> 00:26:42.396
You must keep a promise.

00:26:43.688 --> 00:26:45.230
Thank you.

00:26:45.730 --> 00:26:48.021
Why don't you take them
to a nice restaurant?

00:26:48.105 --> 00:26:52.646
-Like Nomura, a kaiseki restaurant.
-The high-end spot you can't even reserve?

00:26:52.730 --> 00:26:54.855
-Yes.
-No, not those expensive restaurants.

00:26:54.938 --> 00:26:57.646
No, no, Attorney Karasuma.
Don't hold back.

00:26:57.730 --> 00:27:01.480
I'd like to treat you too, as a token
of appreciation for your hard work.

00:27:01.563 --> 00:27:03.688
I'm fine.

00:27:03.771 --> 00:27:07.688
I don't want to be treated by someone
who's an accomplice to the yakuza.

00:27:08.188 --> 00:27:10.896
I don't think the food is to blame.

00:27:11.563 --> 00:27:12.813
Right, Attorney Karasuma?

00:27:12.896 --> 00:27:14.271
I actually agree with that.

00:27:14.355 --> 00:27:15.855
I recently realized something.

00:27:15.938 --> 00:27:19.438
A hard-earned beef bowl
tastes a lot better

00:27:19.521 --> 00:27:24.563
than a fancy feast bought
with ill-gotten gains.

00:27:26.271 --> 00:27:28.521
I'm sure Black Thunder feels the same way.

00:27:29.105 --> 00:27:30.188
Attorney Kujo,

00:27:30.688 --> 00:27:32.688
why don't we raise our attorney fees?

00:27:34.355 --> 00:27:35.188
Why?

00:27:35.271 --> 00:27:39.938
Because if we get more money,
we won't have to take on thugs' cases.

00:27:41.438 --> 00:27:44.980
Charging 330,000 regardless
of the client is a good thing.

00:27:45.563 --> 00:27:50.521
"There are people who are saved by that.
We don't choose our clients." Right?

00:27:50.605 --> 00:27:52.730
I've heard that so many times.

00:27:52.813 --> 00:27:54.980
I can't change how I do my business.

00:27:55.688 --> 00:27:57.938
Greed will be the death of you, you know?

00:27:58.021 --> 00:28:02.021
Even so, I think we should
choose our clients.

00:28:03.605 --> 00:28:07.271
You've started to speak your mind,
Attorney Karasuma.

00:28:08.230 --> 00:28:11.230
But he won't listen to us anyway.

00:28:11.313 --> 00:28:13.688
Maybe we should have
your mother scold him.

00:28:13.771 --> 00:28:15.271
No, no.

00:28:20.563 --> 00:28:23.146
MR. KYOGOKU

00:28:38.646 --> 00:28:41.605
Sorry to call you out
to a place like this.

00:28:43.438 --> 00:28:45.480
Are you staying at a love hotel?

00:28:45.563 --> 00:28:48.021
There are no windows, it smells moldy,

00:28:48.105 --> 00:28:50.605
and there's bad energy,
so it's depressing.

00:28:51.313 --> 00:28:56.688
Well, I guess since Koyama
was just arrested for fraud,

00:28:56.771 --> 00:28:58.271
it can't be helped.

00:28:59.521 --> 00:29:01.646
You'll have to put up with it for a while.

00:29:03.646 --> 00:29:05.521
But, you know,

00:29:06.396 --> 00:29:09.230
what's the deal with Mr. Koyama
being charged with fraud

00:29:09.313 --> 00:29:11.688
just because I stayed
at a hotel under his name?

00:29:13.021 --> 00:29:17.563
Well, you really saved us
by getting him cut loose in 20 days.

00:29:25.021 --> 00:29:28.063
So what can I do for you today?

00:29:30.188 --> 00:29:33.521
The young guys collected
the protection money…

00:29:35.646 --> 00:29:40.188
and the police framed our boss,
who's serving time as a conspirator.

00:29:40.271 --> 00:29:42.105
While he's serving time!

00:29:44.271 --> 00:29:47.980
I thought this
was another unreasonable case.

00:29:50.480 --> 00:29:52.896
Is this about the boss of Fushimi-gumi?

00:29:52.980 --> 00:29:57.605
The police are seriously trying
to take down our gang.

00:30:03.105 --> 00:30:04.105
The thing is,

00:30:05.313 --> 00:30:11.438
when I told the boss about you,
he became really interested.

00:30:14.063 --> 00:30:18.188
Can you visit him and hear him out?

00:30:24.771 --> 00:30:26.896
Attorney Kujo, we'll drive you.

00:30:27.396 --> 00:30:29.896
-It's okay.
-The underboss told us to.

00:30:29.980 --> 00:30:31.813
I came by car, so it's okay.

00:30:56.105 --> 00:30:58.771
It seems you have something to say,
Attorney Karasuma.

00:30:59.938 --> 00:31:01.521
Please just say it clearly.

00:31:04.980 --> 00:31:07.646
So you've made it all the way to the boss.

00:31:09.313 --> 00:31:10.771
What are you going to do?

00:31:21.230 --> 00:31:23.771
Hello, this is Kujo.

00:31:24.271 --> 00:31:25.688
Attorney Kujo.

00:31:26.188 --> 00:31:30.480
My name is Yamazaki. I'm from Fusei-kai,
a branch of Fushimi-gumi.

00:31:30.980 --> 00:31:35.271
I'm calling because I heard
you represented Mr. Kyogoku.

00:31:36.605 --> 00:31:37.938
How can I help you?

00:31:38.021 --> 00:31:40.855
One of our members
was arrested for robbery,

00:31:40.938 --> 00:31:42.771
so could you help him?

00:31:45.146 --> 00:31:47.688
I can't discuss it on the phone.
Come to my office.

00:31:48.313 --> 00:31:50.271
Thank you very much.

00:32:15.605 --> 00:32:16.980
Attorney Karasuma.

00:32:18.938 --> 00:32:22.771
Let's go eat Japan's top takoyaki today
before we head back.

00:32:26.688 --> 00:32:28.021
Attorney Kujo,

00:32:28.521 --> 00:32:30.771
what do you think about
the current situation?

00:32:34.105 --> 00:32:37.230
We should take on cases
that could set meaningful precedents.

00:32:37.313 --> 00:32:39.188
But recently, Attorney Kujo,

00:32:39.271 --> 00:32:41.730
you're acting like a gofer
for anti-social forces.

00:32:43.730 --> 00:32:44.938
A gofer?

00:32:47.230 --> 00:32:49.396
Being involved as a legal representative

00:32:49.480 --> 00:32:52.146
has given me some insight
into their behaviors.

00:32:53.480 --> 00:32:54.521
Insight?

00:32:56.646 --> 00:32:58.646
They're the kind of people

00:32:58.730 --> 00:33:01.605
who'd easily change their testimony
to protect themselves.

00:33:03.438 --> 00:33:04.980
They'll rat you out someday.

00:33:12.105 --> 00:33:14.146
I heard Inukai was released.

00:33:14.230 --> 00:33:18.896
Yes, someone working security
at a club in Roppongi saw him.

00:33:18.980 --> 00:33:21.563
Why hasn't he contacted me?

00:33:23.771 --> 00:33:26.896
I overheard some bad rumors about Inukai.

00:33:38.980 --> 00:33:40.313
It's been a while.

00:33:40.896 --> 00:33:41.855
Yeah.

00:33:41.938 --> 00:33:43.896
Your junior Ayabe

00:33:44.521 --> 00:33:46.813
took good care of me
in the juvenile prison.

00:33:47.855 --> 00:33:53.646
Juvenile prison is tough
without someone's backing.

00:33:55.188 --> 00:33:59.688
When you lost Mibu's backing,
it must've been hell.

00:34:00.730 --> 00:34:02.146
Yes, it was hell.

00:34:02.646 --> 00:34:04.021
You…

00:34:07.688 --> 00:34:09.355
must have a grudge against Mibu.

00:34:11.688 --> 00:34:12.730
Yes.

00:34:13.230 --> 00:34:16.188
I hate him. I was robbed of 10 years
for a measly 3 million.

00:34:20.438 --> 00:34:23.313
Don't you have a grudge
against him too, Mr. Sugawara?

00:34:23.813 --> 00:34:24.855
I heard…

00:34:27.063 --> 00:34:29.813
that your nursing home business
was going well,

00:34:30.980 --> 00:34:32.855
but he ruined everything.

00:34:37.521 --> 00:34:39.771
Why don't we take
300 million yen from Mibu?

00:34:45.646 --> 00:34:47.730
If he's not willing, we'll kill him.

00:34:55.230 --> 00:34:56.855
Sounds good.

00:35:03.480 --> 00:35:04.938
Attorney Kujo,

00:35:06.063 --> 00:35:11.188
please, at least refuse
the Fushimi-gumi boss's case.

00:35:22.313 --> 00:35:23.563
If you don't refuse…

00:35:26.855 --> 00:35:29.563
then I can't be around you, Attorney Kujo.

00:38:23.688 --> 00:38:28.688
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa